What i have learnt :

1
Desktop vs browser: the native app removes friction one click from dock/taskbar beats opening a new tab every time. Daily use is the whole game in a 60-day challenge.
2
Projects as your lab: Claude Projects keep related chats, files, and context in one place. Treat “60 Days of AI” as your running notebook every day’s work lives here, not scattered across random chats.
3
AI Personality Profile: this isn’t a gimmick it’s your first lesson in context-rich prompting. The more Claude knows about how you think, work, and learn, the more tailored every future answer becomes.
4
Build in public: a public GitHub repo turns daily practice into a portfolio. One README today, one commit per day by Day 60 you have proof of work recruiters and peers can actually see.

  What I did :

